Man Group Plc., the worldâ€™s largest
publicly traded hedge fund, hired Scott Kerson as head of
commodities for its Man Systematic Strategies team in  London ,
which was created last year.  He reports to group head Sandy Rattray, formerly a managing
director at Goldman Sachs Group Inc. Kerson joined in November,
spokesman Stephen White, said by e-mail today.  Kerson was the owner of Alpha Dog Commodities LLC., a
California-based consultancy which focused on quantitative
analysis of the global commodity markets, from 2009 to 2011. He
previously worked as a trader at Ospraie Management LLC,
Amaranth Advisors LLC, and Standard Bank Group Ltd. in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
